text:
@wesbos Nice, I like this approach too:

&amp; + &amp; {
  border-left: 1px solid;
}

This produces:

.el.el {
  //
}

Great Sassy way to easily double up selector specificity without repeating selectors:

.el {
  @at-root #{&amp;}#{&amp;} {
    //
  }
}

My favourite:

.wrapper {
  width: 90%;
  max-width: 1200px; // Arbitrary no
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}
